The paper deals with the efficient learnability of geometric concept classes, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of concentration bounds and moment assumptions, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses spectral methods for outlier detection, which is a technique commonly used in computational complexity (cs.CC).
